This section describes how to install Gluster Virtual Storage Appliance
for Xen.

*To install the Gluster Virtual Storage Appliance*

1.  Launch the Citrix XenCenter. The XenCenter main screen appears. +
 +
2.  Select the Xen Server from the list. The *Connect to Server* dialog
may appear if the Remember Password option is not selected. +
 +
+
Error creating thumbnail: Unable to save thumbnail to destination
+
 +
 +
3.  Provide login credentials and click *Connect*. The XenCentre main
screen appears.
4.  Choose *File > Import*. The *Import Wizard* launches. +
 +
+
Error creating thumbnail: Unable to save thumbnail to destination
+
 +
 +
5.  Browse and select the Gluster XVA and click *Next*. +
 +
+
Error creating thumbnail: Unable to save thumbnail to destination
+
 +
 +
6.  Follow the on-screen instructions and in *Select a home server for
the new VM* screen, select the home server and click *Import*. +
 +
7.  In *Configure virtual network interfaces for the new VM* screen,
select the network and click *Finish* in *Complete the import* screen to
complete the wizard. +
 +
+
Error creating thumbnail: Unable to save thumbnail to destination
+
 +
 +
After you complete the wizard, the appliance is downloaded and added to
the XenServer host virtual machine inventory as
*Gluster-Virtual-Storage-Appliance-3-2-0-Template*.

